BAUCHI – A Political Pressure Group known as North-East APC Vanguard for Buhari has endorsed the minister of Niger Delta, Godswill Akpabio for the presidential race under the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC). This was contained in a press statement, issued and signed by the Chairman of the group, Alhaji Ahmed Mohammed, which was made available to newsmen in Bauchi on Monday. According to the statement, the former Governor of Akwa Ibom has done exceptionally well when he was the Governor for Akwa Ibom and now as a Minister, demonstrating a clear example of leadership . 2023: Unity Of Our Party, My Paramount Interest, Not Election… Don’t Turn Osun To Battle Ground, IPAC Cautions Parties “It is now time to support people from the South among which Godswill Akpabio is the only trusted person, he is a sincere and focused leader that has the Youths, the people and the country at heart”. “We are call on him to come out and declare his interest to contest for the president of our dear country comes 2023, we will support him fully, we have already started consultation across our states, our leaders have already shown love and concern on Akpabio because of his tract records to the development, unity and progress of Nigeria, Akpabio is the leader that this country needed at this material time”. “Akpabio has all it takes to lead this country to the promise land, realize the dream of our past leaders as he is the leader and the man for the Job come 2023. Akpoabio is a highly composed person that can lead this country without rancor or discrimination, he is a philanthropist and Nationalist, he is fit for the office” The statement read in parts The Chairman said that, the group will soon mobilize to storm Abuja in order to present its letter of intent to support his aspiration to him so that he will know that they are serious with the project.